  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Through FY2026 to date, federal contract obligations in Alabama total $9.6B across 71,400 awards with an average award size of $135K. Obligations fell 46.9% year over year; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical annual obligations show growth from $13.1B in FY21 to $18.1B in FY25, followed by $9.6B in FY26. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer at $6.8B in FY2026 to date, and the National Aeronautics and Space Administration is the next-largest buyer at $1.5B. Major contractors receiving FY2026 to date obligations include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION and THE BOEING COMPANY at $1B each, and NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION at $435M. Leading industry categories by obligations in FY2026 to date include Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences (except Nanotechnology and Biotechnology) at $3.1B and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $1.2B. Other notable FY2026 to date industries include Engineering Services at $842M and Ship Building and Repairing at $580M.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has federal contracting in Alabama changed recently?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 46.9% year over year in FY2026 to date, with total obligations of $9.6B. That follows a sequence of annual obligations of $13.1B in FY21, $14.1B in FY22, $14.9B in FY23, $17.3B in FY24, and $18.1B in FY25. The FY2026 to date total is a partial, fiscal year to date figure."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies and vendors dominate federal contracting in Alabama?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense is the largest buyer at $6.8B, followed by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration at $1.5B; the Department of Homeland Security and the General Services Administration follow with $370M and $351M respectively. Top vendors in FY2026 to date include LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION and THE BOEING COMPANY at $1B each, NORTHROP GRUMMAN SYSTEMS CORPORATION at $435M, and SCIENCE APPLICATIONS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION at $409M."
      }
    ]
  },
